30/12/2010
ATHENS, Greece -- Police in the western port city of Patra announced on Wednesday (December 29th) the arrests of 74 illegal migrants hidden in two vehicles, a tanker and a cargo truck. 
The migrants, 46 men, two women and 26 minors, were heading eventually to a ferry bound for Italy. 
Some of them were hidden in the tanker's empty cistern, while the rest were hidden in empty boxes aboard the truck. 
The drivers of both vehicles were arrested. 
Police are investigating whether they are a part of an international human trafficking network. 
(DPA, Kathimerini, Inews, Ethnos, News In - 29/12/10)
